{"id":12760,"date":"2025-12-06T07:33:38","date_gmt":"2025-12-06T04:33:38","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/emuseum.torus.kz\/exhibit\/68db596646c470af3-en\/"},"modified":"2025-12-31T12:55:05","modified_gmt":"2025-12-31T09:55:05","slug":"68db596646c470af3-en","status":"publish","type":"exhibit","link":"https:\/\/e-museum.kz\/en\/exhibit\/68db596646c470af3-en\/","title":{"rendered":"Identification badge"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>It belongs to the writer Ali Iskabay. The certificate was issued with a badge on April 10, 1970, in honor of the 100th anniversary of Vladimir Lenin&#8217;s birth. This is a document confirming the awarding of the Order of Valorous Labor (For Valorous Labor). The certificate has a two-page foldable booklet in white and yellow, made of cardboard.<br \/>\nThe breast badge is made of metal, yellow in color, round in shape, marked on the front with the years of V. I. Lenin&#8217;s life 1870-1970, and inside the circle in the middle there is a statue of Lenin&#8217;s head. The upper part of the breast badge is wrapped with a red ribbon with a loop at the back for attachment to the chest.<br \/>\nDate: 1970<br \/>\nTechnique: factory production<br \/>\nSize: ID card width is 7.5 cm, and the vertical dimension is 10.5 cm; badge width is 3 cm, and the vertical dimension is 6 cm<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":0,"menu_order":0,"template":"","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"default","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","ast-disable-related-posts":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-sti